article.headline: Eastern Illinois 60, SE Missouri State 49
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Bobby Catchings scored 18 points and Josh Gomes added 13 to lead Eastern Illinois over Southeast Missouri State 60-49 on Wednesday night. The Panthers (6-18, 5-13 OVC) double- and triple-teamed the Ohio Valley Conference's leading scorer, Roy Booker, the entire contest, holding him to 15 points on 4-of-16 from the field. Southeast Missouri (6-18, 3-15) couldn't find another scorer to step up, and trailed 23-12 with 7 minutes left in the first half. Eastern Illinois went into halftime with a 30-21 lead. The Redhawks rallied in the second half to trim the lead to 46-43 with 4:37 to play, but on the next possession, Gomes was fouled as he hit a 3-pointer for the Panthers. He converted the four-point play to put Eastern Illinois back up 50-43 with 4:13 remaining. Southeast Missouri couldn't answer and after another Panther basket, never got closer than nine points the rest of the game.
